# CI and deployment

- **Unit tests:** `npm run test:unit` (Vitest). Config: `vitest.config.ts`, tests under `src/__tests__/`.
- **E2E:** `@playwright/test` in `devDependencies`. Config: `playwright.config.ts`. CI runs `npm run test:e2e:ci` (project `chromium` only). When `CI=true`, Playwright starts `npm run start` via `webServer` after `npm run build`.
- **Prettier:** `npm run format` / `npm run format:check`. CI uses **`npm run format:check:ci`** (smaller path set) because full `format:check` still flags ~400+ legacy files.
- **ESLint:** `npm run lint` = `next lint` (full app, may have debt). CI uses **`npm run lint:ci`** = ESLint on `src/__tests__` only for a green gate.
- **GitHub Actions:** `.github/workflows/ci.yml` — test job on PR + push; **Vercel production deploy** only on `push` to `main` (needs `VERCEL_*` secrets). Details: `docs/CI_GITHUB_VERCEL.md`.

When editing the workflow, keep `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` build-time env in mind for `next build` on GitHub runners.
